                                    <p style="display: inline;">Cell phone(s) or electronic device(s)</p>
                                </li>
                                <li style="padding-top: 5pt;padding-left: 25pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">
                                    <p style="display: inline;">Other contraband or evidence</p>
                                </li>
                            </ol>
                        </li>
                        <li style="padding-top: 5pt;padding-left: 20pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">
                            <p style="display: inline;">Additional Data Regarding Type of Property Seized.</p>
                            <ol id="l47">
                                <li id="999-226-a-12-d-1" style="padding-top: 5pt;padding-left: 25pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">
                                    <p style="display: inline;">“Basis for Property Seizure.” If the officer seized property during the stop, regardless of whether the property belonged to the person stopped, the officer shall report the basis for the property seizure by selecting all of the following data values that apply:</p>
                               
                                <ol id="l48">
                                    <li style="padding-top: 5pt;padding-left: 30pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">
                                        <p style="display: inline;">Safekeeping as allowed by law/statute</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li style="padding-top: 5pt;padding-left: 30pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">
                                        <p style="display: inline;">Contraband</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li style="padding-top: 5pt;padding-left: 30pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">
                                        <p style="display: inline;">Evidence</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li style="padding-top: 5pt;padding-left: 30pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">
                                        <p style="display: inline;">Impound of vehicle</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li style="padding-top: 5pt;padding-left: 30pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">
                                        <p style="display: inline;">Abandoned Property</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ol>
                                 </li>   
                                <li id="999-226-a-12-d-2" style="padding-top: 5pt;padding-left: 25pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">
                                    <p style="display: inline;">“Type of Property Seized.” If the officer seized property during the stop, regardless of whether the property belonged to the person stopped, the officer shall report the type of property seized, by selecting all of the following data values that apply:</p>
                                    <ol id="l50">
                                        <li style="padding-top: 5pt;padding-left: 30pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">
                                            <p style="display: inline;">Firearm(s)</p>
                                        </li>
